The quarter-finals of the BBC's World Cup of kits is under way.

You can choose your favourites from the four ties below, while you can join the debate on classic kits in our live World Cup page.

Selections for the quarter-finals will close at 15:00 BST.

The original 32 kits were selected by a panel of BBC Sport journalists with former England internationals Danny Mills and Stephen Warnock conducting a draw for the first round.

Republic of Ireland 1990 beat USA 1994 away (61.6% of selections)